[1mDESCRIPTION[0m
     This function registers a callback for a spaceball to report position.  A
     spaceball has six axes of freedom (three of motion and three of orienta-
     tion), plus buttons.  The spaceball allows you to move a control point in
     3D space with a resolution of +/- 1000 units along each of 3 axes.

     The callback is bound to the  current window  .

[1mCAVEATS[0m
     OpenGLUT does not implement spaceball support.

